/* Criticism of compensation on QZ8501 */ new section

Undid revision 675778042 by [[Special:Contributions/SempreVolando|SempreVolando]] ([[User talk:SempreVolando|talk]]) While crash is by Indonesia AirAsia, articles are talking about AirAsia Bhd (Tony Fernandes is owner) handling of compensation.
Unwarranted censorship of relevant and important information by Dmol.
AirAsia Berhad operates all its subsidiaries. CEO Tony Fernandes reponded to the 8501 crash. They are not unrelated. In any case, reference has been made to "Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8051".

How can an airline company be distinct from the air services it provides? Airasia flight 8501 crashed. This is a part of the company's history and should not be censored. And 3 out of 7 stars for safety is a fail grade. Readers ought to know this.

Safety ratings are an important piece of information for any airline company. Airasia has been reported by no less than 2 publications for having low safety ratings. The crash of  flight 8501 is also an important part of the company's history.
Stop censoring relevant information.  Daily Mail is a publication with more than 100 years of history. Airlinerating.com is owned by The Western Australian. Both are reputable publications.
The safety of an airline is important information.
